{
  "stem": "12882.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My father was transferred from Riga all over Germany to Dachau and died about two months before the liberation in Dachau.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There are records in-- in Germany.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And you have to-- if you make claims, you have to find out what this.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I knew about my parents in Riga because one, my mother was a cleaning woman for the officer's barrack and was very much liked.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And one of the officers said he's going to Dresden, and so my mother said, well, wouldn't you like to see my sons and perhaps bring us some winter clothes or something like that?",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He appeared one evening, and we made suitcases and he went back to-- he had letters from my parents.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This had-- these cases have happened in Germany all along.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Doesn't excuse what the others did, but it shows a certain balance that there were decent citizens once in awhile.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I then heard that my mother had died of a heart attack.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I don't know the date, but I heard that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I also heard that after the liberation.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Some people survived.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] This is year before we were deported from Dresden-- was terrible in Dresden-- the Gestapo started visiting us practically every evening.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we were shifted from one Judenhaus to another.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And our belongings which we had became less and less.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But in the one first of the Judenhauses, we lived where my parents even had lived with us, there was a beautiful piano.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I think it was my-- our piano in-- in-- [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And my brother played, and I played.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "So when we had a minute and weren't too tired, we were doing it.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
